tX1S5yyDA1QzeT8PbcLRQyyrMACisBrsCNbKBgYTzQQaSzXaFwAEIOgAkjBcIzLQG7dmCwi4niBCCOQbD8FJMnSrK8q3RWOaCEZlaCKZLn5XVQ1LI9coKvMJpTbQG3zb83lxDUQA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Try ramda version</a></p>\n<p>Click one of the links above to open an online editor. Feel free to make some changes, and see how they affect the output.\nMost pages in this guide will have editable examples like this one.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-about-hello-world\"><a href=\"#what-about-hello-world\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What about Hello World?</h2>\n<p>You might ask why this is the simplest example? The answer is straightforward if you take\na look on our main goal: <em>Simplify implementation of Reusable Redux Components</em>. Newcomers may feel\na little bit lost. No worries. We use Redux to keep state and Counter is the simplest\nexample of something that changes.</p>\n<h2 id=\"whats-the-ramda-tab\"><a href=\"#whats-the-ramda-tab\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What’s the ramda tab?</h2>\n<p>k-frame API was designed to be compatible with auto-curried iteratee-first data-last functions.\n<a href=\"https://ramdajs.com/\">Ramda</a> is a fantastic functional library library for JavaScript programmers which follows this principle.\nOther compatible and very similar option is <a href=\"https://github.com/lodash/lodash/wiki/FP-Guide\">lodash FP</a>.\nRemember, this is just an opt-in, If you don’t like it, don’t feel it or both. Just stick to <em>Plain JS</em> tabs.\n<a href=\"https://ramdajs.com/\">Ramda</a> tabs contains code with the same functionality, but with more functional coding style.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-read-this-guide\"><a href=\"#how-to-read-this-guide\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to Read This Guide </h2>\n<p>In this guide, we will examine the building blocks of k-frame apps: reducers,\nhooks, sagas, forms. Once you master them, you can create complex apps from small reusable pieces.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Tip</p>\n<p>This guide is designed for people who prefer <strong>learning concepts step by step</strong>. If you prefer to learn by doing, check out our <a href=\"/tutorial/tutorial.html\">practical tutorial</a>. You might find this guide and the tutorial complementary to each other.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is the first chapter in a step-by-step guide about main React concepts. You can find a list of all its chapters in the navigation sidebar. If you’re reading this from a mobile device, you can access the navigation by pressing the button in the bottom right corner of your screen.</p>\n<p>Every chapter in this guide builds on the knowledge introduced in earlier chapters. <strong>You can learn most of k-frame by reading the “Main Concepts” guide chapters in the order they appear in the sidebar.</strong> For example, <a href=\"/docs/introducing-scopes.html\">“Introducing Scopes”</a> is the next chapter after this one.</p>\n<h2 id=\"knowledge-level-assumptions\"><a href=\"#knowledge-level-assumptions\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Knowledge Level Assumptions </h2>\n<p>k-frame is a JavaScript framework that connects React, Redux and some other libraries together.\nWe’ll assume you have a basic understanding of how React works and what Reducer is.\nOn the other hand, we’ll try to explain as much as possible inside this documentation.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note</p>\n<p>This guide occasionally uses some of the newer JavaScript syntax in the examples. If you haven’t worked with JavaScript in the last few years, <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/gaearon/683e676101005de0add59e8bb345340c\">these three points</a> should get you most of the way.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"lets-get-started\"><a href=\"#lets-get-started\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Let’s Get Started! </h2>\n<p>Keep scrolling down, and you’ll find the link to the <a href=\"/docs/introducing-scopes.html\">next chapter of this guide</a> right before the website footer.\nf</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Counter","next":"stack-intro.html","prev":"cdn-links.html"},"fields":{"path":"content/docs/counter.md","slug":"docs/counter.html"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"docs/counter.html"}}